<TITLE> 4 killed in Faridpur bus accident </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Faridpur, August 13 (bdnews24.com)  Four people died and 23 were injured on Wednesday on the Bhanga-Maoa highway of Bhanga Upazila in Faridpur when a passenger bus skidded into nearby ditch, police said. Officer in charge (OC) of Bhanga Upazila Police Station Enamul Haque said the incident took place around 7am in the Hashemdia area. The bus was going to Moralganj, Bagerhat from Chittagong. Among the four killed three are women. The two of those who could be identified immediately are Abdul Gafur, 40, of Patia Upazila of Chittagong and Jesmin Akhter, 22, of Rayenda of Bagerhat. Haque said, "The Moralganj-bound bus of Shatbadi Paribahan fell into a roadside ditch when the driver lost control. Four people were killed instantly." Haque also said 15 of the 23 injured people were admitted to Bhanga Upazila Health Centre. He added attempts were being made to retrieve the bus from the ditch, with the driver not to be found anywhere. bdnews2
